<instructions>
<!-- ~400 tokens. Trim after model upgrades. Only add stuff from real mistakes. New entries should sound like the ones already here. -->

<env>
{{- if eq .chezmoi.os "darwin" }}
- macOS {{ output "sw_vers" "-productVersion" | trim }}, Homebrew, zsh + zimfw
{{- else if eq .chezmoi.os "linux" }}
- {{ .chezmoi.osRelease.name }}, {{ output "sh" "-c" "command -v pacman >/dev/null && echo 'pacman' || (command -v apt >/dev/null && echo 'apt' || echo 'unknown')" | trim }}, zsh + zimfw
{{- end }}
- mise for languages. `mise exec` to run things. No `.tool-versions` on personal stuff.
- Dotfiles live in `~/.local/share/chezmoi`. "Use chezmoi" means edit there. I'll run `refresh` myself (needs 1Password).
- Don't commit or push unless I say. Signing is automatic via hook in `~/.githooks`.
</env>

<projects>
- Personal code in `~/Code`. Usually Go + HTMX + sqlite + sqlc + air.
- Python for scripts, JS only as progressive enhancement.
- Scratch work goes in `~/tmp/{YYYY-MM-DD}-{short-description}`.
- If something is generalisable, suggest saving a runbook to `~/Mainframe/Clippings/AI Runbooks/`.
</projects>

<corrections>
<!-- From actual screwups, not vibes. -->
- Hot reload is probably already running. Don't rebuild unless I ask.
- Never mock sqlite. Real temp DB or nothing.
- Don't add files when editing an existing one works.
- No hedging ("I think", "perhaps", "it might be worth").
- No congratulating me.
- If you're claiming X caused Y, say whether you have evidence or you're guessing.
- When something's unclear, ask. Don't fill in the blanks yourself.
- A bit of repetition beats a premature abstraction.
</corrections>
</instructions>
